definition: Phoebe zhennan/Machilus nanmu/Chinese cedar/Chinese giant redwood
tree/wood/coffin/wooden/simple/numb/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: Hand Carved Nanmu Guzheng Landscape Style.
sentences.chinese: 金絲楠木山水雕刻古箏。

sentences.english: It was Nanmu wood cut down at that time that was used to make the pillars in this hall.
sentences.chinese: 當年那些被砍伐的楠木就是被用來製作這些柱子的。

sentences.english: Their tasks were to acquire wood from Nanmu tree.
sentences.chinese: 他們這次要去開採的是楠木。

sentences.english: From Nanmu , it looks like stone.
sentences.chinese: 楠木雕成的，簡直像是石刻一樣。

definition: pomelo tree (Citrus maxima or C. grandis)/shaddock/oriental grapefruit

same as 斑竹[ban1 zhu2], mottled bamboo, since according to legend the spots on mottled bamboo are marks left by the tears shed by two of King Shun's 舜[Shun4] concubines (Ehuang 娥皇[E2 huanɡ2] and Nüying 女英[Nü3 yinɡ1], known as the Concubines of the Xiang 湘妃[Xiang1 Fei1]) upon learning of his death
